# Cursor/Copilot Development Rules for Unity ELD Project

## Project Overview
- **Framework**: React 19 + TypeScript 6 + Vite 8
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.3
- **Routing**: React Router 7 (HashRouter for GitHub Pages)
- **State Management**: React Hooks (useState, useMemo, useCallback)
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui components + custom components
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages

## Code Style Rules

### TypeScript/React
1. **Use functional components** with React hooks only
2. **Always type component props** with interfaces
3. **Use TypeScript strict mode** - all variables/returns must be typed
4. **Avoid `any` type** - use proper typing instead
5. **Import React components** from correct paths
6. **Use arrow functions** for component definitions

### Example Component Structure
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  count: number;
  onAction?: (value: string) => void;
}

export default function MyComponent({ title, count, onAction }: ComponentProps) {
  const [state, setState] = useState(0);

  return (
	<div>
	  {title}
	</div>
  );
}
```

### Tailwind CSS
1. **Use Tailwind classes** for all styling (no CSS files in components)
2. **Dark mode classes** are supported - use `dark:` prefix
3. **Responsive classes** use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` prefixes
4. **Use consistent spacing** - use Tailwind scale (4px base unit)
5. **Color system** - use Tailwind color names (gray-500, blue-600, etc.)

### File Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase (MyComponent.tsx)
- **Hooks**: camelCase starting with 'use' (useLocalStorage.ts)
- **Data/Utilities**: camelCase (drivers.ts, utils.ts)
- **Types**: camelCase with .ts extension (driver.ts for interfaces)
- **Pages**: PascalCase (Dashboard.tsx, Logs.tsx)

### Directory Structure Rules
```
src/
├── pages/           # Page components (full page layouts)
├── components/      # Reusable components
├── routes/          # Router configuration
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks (if needed)
├── utils/          # Utility functions (if needed)
├── types/          # TypeScript interfaces/types
└── data/           # Mock data or constants
```

## Import Organization
```typescript
// 1. React/third-party imports
import { useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";

// 2. Internal imports
import Button from "@/components/Button";
import type { Driver } from "@/types/driver";

// 3. Styles/assets (if any)
import styles from "./Component.module.css";
```

## Component Patterns

### State Management
- Use `useState` for component-level state
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations
- Use `useCallback` for memoized functions
- Avoid prop drilling - pass necessary data only

### Data Fetching
- Use mock data in `src/data/` for now
- Structure: `initialDrivers`, `mockLogsData`, etc.
- Keep data files simple without complex logic

### Props Destructuring
```typescript
// ✅ Good
function Component({ title, items, onClick }: ComponentProps) {
  return <div>{title}</div>;
}

// ❌ Avoid
function Component(props: ComponentProps) {
  return <div>{props.title}</div>;
}
```

## Routing Rules
- **Router**: Use `HashRouter` (GitHub Pages requirement)
- **Protected Routes**: Wrap in `<ProtectedRoute>` component
- **URLs**: Hash-based format `/#/path`
- **Navigation**: Use `useNavigate()` hook from react-router-dom

### Route Structure
```typescript
<HashRouter>
  <Routes>
	<Route path="/" element={<Login />} />
	<Route path="/dashboard" element={<ProtectedRoute><Dashboard /></ProtectedRoute>} />
	<Route path="/dashboard/logs" element={<ProtectedRoute><Logs /></ProtectedRoute>} />
	<Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />
  </Routes>
</HashRouter>
```

## Performance Rules
1. **Memoize expensive operations** with `useMemo`
2. **Memoize callbacks** with `useCallback` when passed to children
3. **Lazy load components** if app grows (React.lazy)
4. **Key prop**: Always provide unique `key` in lists
5. **Conditional rendering**: Use early returns when possible

## Accessibility Rules
1. **Semantic HTML**: Use proper tags (button, nav, main, etc.)
2. **ARIA labels**: Add when needed for screen readers
3. **Color contrast**: Ensure dark mode has proper contrast
4. **Keyboard navigation**: Test with Tab key
5. **Form labels**: Always associate with input elements

## Dark Mode
- All components should support dark mode
- Use `dark:` Tailwind classes
- Check colors: `text-gray-900 dark:text-white`
- Background: `bg-white dark:bg-[#1B2140]`
- Theme toggle in TopHeader component

## Error Handling
```typescript
// ✅ Good error handling
try {
  const data = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("user") || "{}");
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Failed to parse user data", error);
}

// Show user-friendly toast
import { toast } from "sonner";
toast.error("Something went wrong");
```

## Git Commit Messages
- Format: `type: description`
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, style
- Example: `feat: Add Logs page with table and filters`
- Keep messages concise and descriptive

## Build & Deployment
- `npm run dev` - Development server
- `npm run build` - Production build
- `npm run deploy` - Deploy to GitHub Pages
- `npm run lint` - Check code style

## Common Tasks

### Adding New Page
1. Create file in `src/pages/PageName.tsx`
2. Define TypeScript interface for props
3. Add route in `src/routes/router.tsx`
4. Wrap with `ProtectedRoute` if needed
5. Add navigation in Sidebar

### Adding New Component
1. Create file in `src/components/ComponentName.tsx`
2. Define interface for props
3. Use Tailwind for styling
4. Support dark mode with `dark:` classes
5. Export as default

### Adding New Data
1. Create/update file in `src/data/`
2. Define TypeScript types in `src/pages/dashboard/types/`
3. Use in components with proper imports
4. Keep mock data separate from logic

## Linting & Quality
- Run `npm run lint` before commits
- Fix TypeScript errors completely
- No unused imports/variables
- Use proper error boundaries where needed

## Testing Workflow
1. Test in development: `npm run dev`
2. Build locally: `npm run build`
3. Preview build: `npm run preview`
4. Test GitHub Pages deployment

## UI Component Library
- Using **shadcn/ui** components (in `src/components/ui/`)
- Available: Button, Card, Input, Label, Checkbox, etc.
- Custom styled with Tailwind CSS
- Customizable and composable

## Development Mindset
1. **Think in components** - break UI into reusable parts
2. **Data first** - define types before implementation
3. **Mobile first** - design for small screens first
4. **Dark mode first** - consider dark mode in every component
5. **Accessibility first** - semantic HTML and ARIA labels
6. **Performance first** - use React hooks wisely

## When in Doubt
1. Check similar components in project
2. Follow existing patterns
3. Run `npm run lint` to catch issues
4. Test in browser (dev and build)
5. Check GitHub Pages deployment

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- ❌ Using `any` type in TypeScript
- ❌ Forgetting `dark:` classes in styled components
- ❌ Not memoizing in lists (missing `key` prop)
- ❌ Prop drilling too deep
- ❌ Importing from wrong paths
- ❌ Forgetting to add `ProtectedRoute` wrapper
- ❌ Using `BrowserRouter` (must use `HashRouter`)
